commit.message:
Fix behavior of (program_)?regex and (program_)?neg_regex conditions.

Multiple neg_regex required all to match to discard a message. Now only
one must match, allowing patterns to be spread out over several
neg_regex conditions.

Non-matching neg_regex would cause a message to be logged even if all
regex conditions did not match. This now requires at least one regex to
match, or no regex conditions to be given.
